  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the best all round fighter jet as of 2015?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" all-around fighter jet as of 2015 involves considering various factors such as air superiority, multirole capabilities, stealth features, avionics, maneuverability, and operational versatility. Several advanced fighter jets stood out during that period, each excelling in different aspects. Here are some of the top contenders:\n\n### **1. Lockheed Martin F-35 Lightning II**\n- **Role:** Multirole stealth fighter\n- **Overview:** The F-35 was designed to perform a wide range of missions, including air superiority, ground attack, electronic warfare, and intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR). Its stealth capabilities make it less detectable to radar, providing a significant advantage in contested airspaces.\n- **Variants:** The F-35 comes in three variants\u2014the conventional takeoff and landing (CTOL) F-35A, the short takeoff/vertical landing (STOVL) F-35B, and the carrier-based F-35C.\n- **Strengths:** Advanced avionics, sensor fusion, network-centric warfare capabilities, and versatility across different branches of the military.\n\n### **2. Lockheed Martin F-22 Raptor**\n- **Role:** Air superiority fighter\n- **Overview:** The F-22 is renowned for its exceptional stealth, supercruise (the ability to cruise at supersonic speeds without afterburners), and advanced maneuverability. It was primarily designed to establish air dominance by outperforming adversary aircraft.\n- **Strengths:** Superior stealth features, advanced avionics and sensors, unmatched maneuverability, and formidable weapons systems.\n\n### **3. Eurofighter Typhoon**\n- **Role:** Multirole fighter\n- **Overview:** Developed by a consortium of European countries, the Eurofighter Typhoon is a highly agile aircraft designed for both air-to-air combat and ground attack missions. It emphasizes agility and high performance in various combat scenarios.\n- **Strengths:** Excellent maneuverability, advanced avionics and sensors, versatility in mission profiles, and integration of modern weaponry.\n\n### **4. Dassault Rafale**\n- **Role:** Multirole fighter\n- **Overview:** The Rafale, developed by France's Dassault Aviation, is known for its flexibility and capability to perform a wide array of missions, including air supremacy, interdiction, reconnaissance, and nuclear deterrence.\n- **Strengths:** Advanced avionics, strong multirole performance, superior payload capacity, and proven combat capabilities in various conflicts.\n\n### **5. Sukhoi Su-35S**\n- **Role:** Multirole fighter with a strong emphasis on air superiority\n- **Overview:** The Su-35S is an advanced variant of the Russian Su-27 family, featuring improved avionics, thrust-vectoring engines for enhanced maneuverability, and a potent array of weapons.\n- **Strengths:** Exceptional agility, powerful engines, advanced radar and sensor systems, and significant payload capacity.\n\n### **Considerations in Determining \"Best\"**\nWhile each of these aircraft has its unique strengths, the \"best\" all-round fighter jet often depends on specific mission requirements, the strategic needs of the operating country, and interoperability with existing systems. For instance:\n\n- **Stealth and Advanced Technology:** The F-35 and F-22 excel in stealth and advanced sensor integration, making them ideal for modern, high-threat environments.\n- **Maneuverability and Performance:** The F-22 and Su-35S are standout performers in terms of agility and air combat capabilities.\n- **Multirole Versatility:** The Eurofighter Typhoon and Dassault Rafale offer exceptional flexibility across a wide range of missions, balancing air-to-air and air-to-ground roles effectively.\n\n### **Conclusion**\nAs of 2015, there wasn't a unanimous consensus on a single \"best\" all-round fighter jet, as each aircraft excelled in different areas catering to varied strategic needs. The Lockheed Martin F-35 Lightning II was often highlighted for its comprehensive multirole capabilities and stealth features, making it a strong candidate for the title of the best all-around fighter jet. However, air superiority-focused jets like the F-22 Raptor, and other versatile fighters like the Eurofighter Typhoon and Dassault Rafale, were also highly regarded for their specific strengths.\n\nUltimately, the choice of the best all-round fighter jet depends on the specific priorities and requirements of the purchasing country or military force.",
